This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for executable AST semantics.

## Core concept

Expressions produce values. Statements control execution. Receiving contexts decide when a natural value may be coerced.

## Beanstalk boundary

AST body checking owns:

- natural expression types
- explicit receiving boundaries
- calls, fields and receiver lookup
- access-mode validation
- value-producing blocks
- receiver arity
- function terminality

Value-producing `if`, match and block-form `catch` are closed producers rather than general expressions.

Fresh values may satisfy exclusive parameters through compiler-created HIR locals. Source `~` remains place-only access syntax.

## Rewrite focus

Explain expression versus statement position, contextual typing, control-flow terminality and why user diagnostics belong before HIR.

Canonical details live in the compiler and language authorities.
